[Nouns] counter evidence; evidence on the other side, evidence on the other hand; conflicting evidence; disproof, refutation [more]; negation [more].
plea [more]; vindication [more] counter protest; "tu quoque" argument; other side of the shield, other side of the coin, reverse of the shield.
[Verbs] countervail, oppose; rebut (refute) [more]; subvert (destroy) [more]; cheek, weaken; contravene; contradict (deny) [more]; tell another story, turn the scale, alter the case; turn the tables; cut both ways; prove a negative.
audire alteram partem.
[Adjectives] countervailing; contradictory.
unattested, unauthenticated, unsupported by evidence; supposititious.
[Adverbs] on the contrary, per contra.
